51.1	Ant%C3%B3nio_Dam%C3%A1sio	António Damásio	Antonio Damasio (born February 25, 1944 in Lisbon, Portugal) is David Dornsife Professor of Neuroscience at the University of Southern California, where he heads USC's Brain and Creativity Institute and Adjunct Professor at the Salk Institute. Prior to taking up his posts at USC, in 2005, Damasio was M.W. Van Allen Professor and Head of Neurology at the University of Iowa Hospitals and Clinics. His career at Iowa lasted from 1976 to 2005.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6b/Antonio_Damasio.jpg/220px-Antonio_Damasio.jpg
